$ /usr/local

According to the → Linux/fhs, `/opt` is for «for use by the system administrator when installing software locally».
Compare with → Linux/fhs/opt and → Linux/fhs/usr.

→ development/GNU-Build-System/configure chooses this directory as default for *architecture independent* 
(overwriteable with → development/GNU-Build-System/configure#opt-prefix) and *architecture dependent* files
(overwriteable with → development/GNU-Build-System/configure#opt-exec-prefix).
